Ward Ferry Management LTD Cut China Lodging Group LTD (HTHT) Holding By $25.31 Million, Now (DNOW) SI Increased By 10.66%

July 24, 2017 - By Adrian Mccoy

Ward Ferry Management Ltd decreased China Lodging Group Ltd (HTHT) stake by 22.15% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Ward Ferry Management Ltd sold 496,291 shares as China Lodging Group Ltd (HTHT)’s stock rose 35.67%. The Ward Ferry Management Ltd holds 1.74 million shares with $90.41 million value, down from 2.24M last quarter. China Lodging Group Ltd now has $6.70 billion valuation. The stock rose 2.66% or $2.49 reaching $96. About 78,340 shares traded. China Lodging Group, Ltd (ADR) (NASDAQ:HTHT) has risen 127.67% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 110.97% the S&P500.






 Now Incorporated (NYSE:DNOW) had an increase of 10.66% in short interest. DNOW’s SI was 9.15M shares in July as released by FINRA. Its up 10.66% from 8.27 million shares previously. With 1.41M avg volume, 7 days are for Now Incorporated (NYSE:DNOW)’s short sellers to cover DNOW’s short positions. The SI to Now Incorporated’s float is 8.66%. About 152,784 shares traded. NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW) has risen 9.86% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 6.84% the S&P500.
Investors sentiment increased to 0.96 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.01, from 0.95 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 32 investors sold NOW Inc shares while 88 reduced holdings. 38 funds opened positions while 77 raised stakes. 107.32 million shares or 1.48% less from 108.93 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Lord Abbett & Limited Liability stated it has 477,990 shares. Beddow Mgmt Inc owns 64,863 shares or 0.53% of their US portfolio. Moreover, South Dakota Inv Council has 0.01% invested in NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW) for 27,900 shares. Moreover, Bank Of America Corporation De has 0% invested in NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW) for 782,121 shares. Hallmark Capital Mngmt holds 0% or 36 shares in its portfolio. Rbo Co Llc reported 389,494 shares. Deutsche Retail Bank Ag holds 151,464 shares or 0% of its portfolio. Sasco Capital Ct owns 39,520 shares for 0.02% of their portfolio. Iat Reinsurance Ltd stated it has 1,100 shares. Great Lakes Advisors Limited Liability reported 0.1% of its portfolio in NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW). Employees Retirement Association Of Colorado holds 0% or 22,776 shares in its portfolio. Evercore Wealth Management Limited Liability Co, New York-based fund reported 1,925 shares. 21,000 are owned by Omers Administration. Neuberger Berman Gp Ltd Limited Liability Company owns 929,580 shares for 0.03% of their portfolio. Waverton Investment has invested 0.01% of its portfolio in NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW).
Since March 7, 2017, it had 2 buys, and 0 insider sales for $187,613 activity. 5,264 shares were bought by EADS RODNEY W, worth $99,963. Shares for $87,650 were bought by Crandell James.
Among 11 analysts covering Now Inc (NYSE:DNOW), 6 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 5 Hold. Therefore 55% are positive. Now Inc had 20 analyst reports since August 6, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Seaport Global upgraded NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW) on Thursday, May 4 to “Buy” rating. The stock has “Market Perform” rating by Cowen & Co on Friday, September 16. Stephens downgraded NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW) rating on Thursday, August 6. Stephens has “Equal Weight” rating and $19 target. On Wednesday, February 24 the stock rating was maintained by JP Morgan with “Neutral”. The company was maintained on Monday, May 29 by KeyCorp. On Wednesday, June 21 the stock rating was downgraded by Seaport Global to “Neutral”. The stock has “Positive” rating by Susquehanna on Tuesday, January 10. Stifel Nicolaus maintained the shares of DNOW in report on Thursday, July 6 with “Buy” rating. Robert W. Baird upgraded it to “Outperform” rating and $22 target in Wednesday, April 26 report. The stock of NOW Inc (NYSE:DNOW) earned “Neutral” rating by Credit Suisse on Tuesday, September 15.



